<h3>Family Resources</h3>
<p>Arizona Together is committed to providing families access to resources that they need during this time. If you are interested in learning more, volunteering, or donating please visit <a href="https://arizonatogether.org/">https://arizonatogether.org/</a></p>
<p>Cox Internet is offering 1 month of free internet access to households with school-age students through their Connect2Compete program (following the one-month period, the cost will be $9.95/mo)<br> To set up your free access, please refer to the following link <a href="https://www.cox.com/residential/internet/connect2compete.html">https://www.cox.com/residential/internet/connect2compete.html</a> and input the requested information. If you need assistance during the application process, you can call the school for support.</p>
<p>Xfinity is offering internet options for students and families in the form of public access to hotspots. Hotspots are located within small businesses and outdoors in commercial areas.<br> i. To find the Xfinity hotspot near you, visit <a href="https://wifi.xfinity.com/">https://wifi.xfinity.com/</a> and enter your zip code.<br> ii. Once at a hotspot, select the “xfinitywifi” network name in the list of available internets and then launch your browser.</p>
